---
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
import OpenPrinterStatus from '../components/OpenPrinterStatus.astro';
---

<SiteLayout
  title="No Lock-In Printer"
  description="Independent printer buying guides for avoiding ink subscriptions, cartridge lock-in, firmware surprises, and weak Linux support."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <img
      src="/images/printer-workflow.svg"
      width="1600"
      height="900"
      alt="Illustration of a printer using local connections and refill supplies"
      fetchpriority="high"
      decoding="async"
    />
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hero-content">
        <p class="eyebrow">Independent printer buying intelligence</p>
        <h1>Buy a printer that does not own you back.</h1>
        <p class="hero-copy">
          No Lock-In Printer tracks subscription-free printers, refillable ink systems, Linux-friendly models, and the still-unproven OpenPrinter project.
        </p>
        <div class="actions">
          <a class="button" href="/guides/no-subscription-printers/">Start with buyer picks</a>
          <a class="button secondary" href="/openprinter/">Check OpenPrinter status</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--amber);">Two-track strategy</p>
          <h2>Today’s documented choices, tomorrow’s open hardware.</h2>
        </div>
        <p>
          The site is built around a durable commercial core, with OpenPrinter used as a high-interest frontier topic rather than the whole business.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid-2">
        <article class="card feature-card">
          <div class="card-body">
            <div class="tag-row">
              <span class="tag">Commercial core</span>
              <span class="tag amber">Buy now</span>
            </div>
            <h3>The Resistance</h3>
            <p class="muted">
              Practical guides for people who want refillable ink, no mandatory subscriptions, predictable toner, and fewer firmware surprises.
            </p>
            <div class="actions">
              <a class="button" href="/guides/no-subscription-printers/">View no-subscription picks</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="card feature-card">
          <div class="card-body">
            <div class="tag-row">
              <span class="tag">Frontier tracker</span>
              <span class="tag brick">Not launched</span>
            </div>
            <h3>The Frontier</h3>
            <p class="muted">
              A sober OpenPrinter tracker that separates confirmed facts from wishful thinking: no confirmed price, no release date, and licensing limits to understand.
            </p>
            <div class="actions">
              <a class="button" href="/openprinter/">Open status board</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="container split">
      <OpenPrinterStatus />
      <div class="panel">
        <div class="panel-inner">
          <p class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--amber);">How the shortlist works</p>
          <h2>Evidence before recommendations</h2>
          <p class="muted">
            Four models are compared through the same six ownership questions. We do not convert unknowns into points or claim independently tested results.
          </p>
          <ul class="status-list">
            <li>Can ordinary supplies be purchased outside a subscription?</li>
            <li>Which USB, Ethernet, Wi-Fi Direct, or local protocols are documented?</li>
            <li>What remains unknown about accounts, firmware, and third-party supplies?</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--amber);">Documented shortlist</p>
          <h2>Four different ownership tradeoffs.</h2>
        </div>
        <p>Each summary is based on current U.S. manufacturer documents and states what we did not independently test.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid-2 shortlist-grid">
        <article class="card"><div class="card-body"><h3>Brother MFC-J4335DW</h3><p class="muted">Color office functions and ordinary LC406 cartridges alongside an optional subscription path.</p><a href="/guides/no-subscription-printers/#brother-mfc-j4335dw">Review the cartridge boundary</a></div></article>
        <article class="card"><div class="card-body"><h3>Epson EcoTank ET-2850</h3><p class="muted">Refill tanks and automatic duplex; do not confuse the retail model with subscription-only ET-2850U.</p><a href="/guides/no-subscription-printers/#epson-ecotank-et-2850">Review the model distinction</a></div></article>
        <article class="card"><div class="card-body"><h3>Canon PIXMA G3270</h3><p class="muted">Refillable GI-21 tanks and Wireless Direct, but simplex document printing and unclear account-free setup.</p><a href="/guides/no-subscription-printers/#canon-pixma-g3270">Review the documented limits</a></div></article>
        <article class="card"><div class="card-body"><h3>Brother HL-L2460DW</h3><p class="muted">Monochrome laser with Ethernet, local protocols, and Linux explicitly listed by Brother.</p><a href="/guides/no-subscription-printers/#brother-hl-l2460dw">Review the Linux option</a></div></article>
      </div>
      <div class="actions">
        <a class="button" href="/guides/no-subscription-printers/">Read the sourced buying guide</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
